# {{ project_name }}

## Project Structure

This is a Swift + TypeScript monorepo: SwiftUI multiplatform app + Hono REST API.

- `apps/mobile/` — SwiftUI multiplatform app (iOS, iPadOS, macOS, visionOS)
- `apps/api/` — Hono REST API (TypeScript, managed with pnpm)
- `packages/db/` — Prisma database schema and client
- `packages/types/` — Shared TypeScript types
- `packages/config/` — Shared TypeScript configuration

## Commands

### TypeScript (API)
- `pnpm dev` — Start API dev server
- `pnpm build` — Build all TS packages
- `pnpm test` — Run all TS tests (Vitest)
- `pnpm lint` — Lint with Biome
- `pnpm typecheck` — TypeScript type checking
- `pnpm db:push` — Push Prisma schema to database
- `pnpm db:studio` — Open Prisma Studio

### Swift (Mobile)
- `cd apps/mobile && xcodegen generate` — Generate Xcode project
- Open `apps/mobile/{{ swift_project_name }}.xcodeproj` in Xcode
- Build and run from Xcode (Cmd+R)
- Run tests from Xcode (Cmd+U)

## Development

1. `docker compose up -d` — Start Postgres
2. `pnpm install` — Install TS dependencies
3. `pnpm db:push` — Push database schema
4. `pnpm dev` — Start API server
5. `cd apps/mobile && xcodegen generate` — Generate Xcode project
6. Open in Xcode and run

## API

- REST API serves all routes under `/api` prefix
- Health check: `GET /api/health`
- User CRUD: `GET /api/users`, `POST /api/users`
- The Swift app connects to the API via `APIClient` (URLSession + Codable)

## Conventions

### TypeScript (apps/api/, packages/)
- Strict TypeScript (`strict: true`)
- Biome for linting and formatting
- All packages use workspace protocol (`workspace:*`)
- Every app and package has at least one test

### Swift (apps/mobile/)
- Swift 6.0, SwiftUI for all views
- XcodeGen for project generation (never edit .xcodeproj directly)
- Swift Testing framework for unit tests
- URLSession + Codable for API communication (no third-party networking libs)
